title: Grateful Dead Live at Miami Arena on 1994-04-06
description: Jack Straw, Jack A Roe, Wang Dang Doodle, Broken Arrow, West L.A. Fadeaway, El Paso*, Row Jimmy, Promised Land Here Comes Sunshine, Samson & Delilah, Cumberland Blues, Way to Go Home, Women Are Smarter, Drums-> Space-> The Wheel, All Along The Watchtower, Standing On the Moon, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Comes a Time Only listened to the Comes a Time, but it's cool to hear Jerry instruct Vince how to play the tune in the middle of it.

1st show i attended Definitely has some great moments but far from the best show I have heard. But hey, imo, no GD show is ever a bad show Love West L.A Fadeaway, cool Drums/Space ,Cumberland Blues, Samson & Delilah and Standing On The Moon. Rest in peace, Jerry G and Vince...
Great show The venue was in a shady section the locals where selling dubs of crack out front! my boy got lost in the Homestead and hitched back to Ft Lauderdale in one piece amazing
